    <p class="text-lg py-4 pl-70 text-darkblue" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="2000">In 2017,
        <strong>Konnex</strong> hired an independent environmental engineering company to conduct baseline studies.
        Since then, the company has tracked and studied a variety of elements of the environment including climate and
        air quality, surface and groundwater hydrology, soil characterization, transportation, water use and treatment,
        plant and wildlife, community and infrastructure planning, and much more. This data has helped Konnex understand
        the existing environmental conditions before the start of mining activities and will continue serving as a guide
        for Konnex’s development plans. It will also serve as a benchmark for reclamation at the end of the mine life.
