<div class="col-md-12 pb-100 mx-5 ms-50">
    <h2 class="mb-4 my-60" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="2000">Social Responsibility</h2>
    <p class="text-md mb-5 mx-4" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="2000">Konnex Resources is
        committed to creating and maintaining partnerships in the communities close to its operations. We recognize that
        people living in Custer and Butte counties have unique perspectives that deserve to be represented in
        decision-making processes throughout the life of our activities in central Idaho. Konnex leaders intend to
        continue providing opportunities to participate in direct and transparent communications with all stakeholders
        to engage the community and to make our operations the best they can be.</p>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <h4>Konnex Community Advisory Team</h4>
        </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-md mb-5 mx-4">The Konnex Community Advisory Team (KCAT) is made up of 10 independent residents of
        Custer and Butte
        counties and three representatives from Konnex Resources. The mission of KCAT is to create an enduring
        model of partnership, transparency, and accountability between Konnex and the local communities.
    </p>
    <p class="text-md mb-5 mx-4">
        KCAT meets regularly to discuss the opportunities and challenges created as a result of Konnex
        Resources’ operations in Custer County. The committee members have a wide range of experiences and were
        selected to represent the diverse backgrounds of the people living near the Project area. KCAT is tasked
        with creating a ‘Good Neighbor Agreement’ between Konnex and the community, presenting questions and
        concerns from peers to Konnex management, distributing Konnex-sponsored scholarships and community
        funds, and more.
    </p>
    <p class="text-md mb-5 mx-4">
        Anyone living within Custer and Butte Counties is welcome to apply for KCAT’s next open position.
    </p>
    <a class="red-btn mx-4" href="#" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="2000">Apply for KCAT</a>
    <ul class='pt-120'>
        <li>
            <h4>Investing in Opportunities</h4>
        </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-md mb-5 mx-4">Konnex Resources is proud to invest in the people and community programs that make
        Custer and Butte counties great places to live and work. Each year, Konnex provides funding to support local
        sporting events, community programs, and scholarship awards. Our geologists also provide educational
        opportunities for local high school students as a way to foster an interest in mining activities and inspire an
        enthusiasm for future education and career opportunities the industry can provide.
    </p>
    <a class="red-btn mx-4" href="#" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="2000">Apply for Community Funds</a>
    <a class="red-btn mx-4" href="#" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="2000">Apply for Scholarships</a>
</div>
<div class="col-md-12 pb-100 mx-5 ms-50">
    <h2 class="mb-4 my-60" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="2000">Corporate Governance</h2>
    <h3 class='pb-3' style='color:black'>Konnex Resources and its parent company, Phoenix Copper Limited, share a firm
        set of corporate policies and promote best practices at every level of our operations that meet and exceed what
        is required by law.
    </h3>
    <p class="text-lg py-4 text-darkblue" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="2000">We are fortunate to be
        operating in an area where the mining industry is highly regulated to protect the environment, employees, and
        communities surrounding the operations. We also recognize that residents of Mackay, Idaho and its neighboring
        cities enjoy a unique way of life and culture that requires protection beyond what is written in law. For this
        reason, Konnex has asked the members of the Konnex Community Advisory Team to draft a ‘Good Neighbor Agreement.’
        The Good Neighbor Agreement will be developed by the community representatives, with input from their peers, as
        formal commitment between the Company and the community. It will allow for community interests to be properly
        represented as we work to set the gold standard for our operations, employment practices, and more.</p>
    <ul class='ml-120' data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="2000">
        <li>Our Policies</li>
        <li>Whistleblower Policy</li>
        <li>Code of Conduct & Ethical Values Policy</li>
        <li>Anti-bribery & Anti-corruption Policy</li>
        <li>Charitable Donations Policy</li>
        <li>Insider Trading & Reporting Policy</li>
        <li>Diversity Policy</li>
    </ul>

</div>
